---
import Layout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
---
<Layout title="Home">

    <p>
        These pages use <code>astro@0.22.20</code>.
    </p>

    <h2>No problem</h2>
    <p>
        In <code>astro@0.22.20</code>, markdown files can be imported and displayed as if if they were components out of the box.
    </p>

    <p>
        I like.
    </p>

        <pre>
---
import Content from "../path/to/content/about.md";
---

&lt;Content /&gt;
        </pre>

    <p>
        This does not work in <code>astro@1.0.0-beta.5</code>.
    </p>

<hr />

Do

<ul>
<li>
    <pre>
git checkout master && npm run start:clean</pre>
to see how it works in <code>v1.0.0-beta.5</code>.
</li>
<li>
    <pre>
git checkout astro-v1.0.0-beta.5-react && npm run start:clean</pre>
to see how it works in <code>v1.0.0-beta.5</code> <em>with a React integration registered</em>.
</li>
</ul>

</Layout>
